68190.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
68190.description: Aang learns that he must go to the Fire Nation temple during the winter solstice if he wishes to speak with Avatar Roku to see what he must do. However, with Prince Zuko on his trail while he heads straight into the heart of the nation who wants him captured, he realizes that this isn't going to be an easy task. Will Aang be able to talk to Avatar Roku before Zuko finds him?

68191.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
68191.description: After Katara attempts to teach Aang waterbending, she is desperate to improve her abilities. When Katara inadvertently stumbles across a waterbending scroll that can help improve her ability while Aang is looking at a pirate's store, she decides to steal it after she realizes that she couldn't hope to afford it; but will she be capable of stealing from the pirates without causing herself and her friends trouble?

68192.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68192.description: The long-lost episode of Mermaid Man is finally showing on TV, but will SpongeBob make it home in time to watch? // Karen gets a computer virus, and it's up to SpongeBob to get it out of her!

68193.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68193.description: When a gang of kids steals the Krusty Krab's grill, SpongeBob and Mr. Krabs go to extreme lengths to win it back. // SpongeBob helps out the Krusty Krab's night shift crew, but the customers crave something creepier than usual.

68194.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
68194.description: At home, Mikey always messes things up, but when the Turtles go to the bizarre realm of Dimension X, he's the only one who can figure the place out.

68195.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
68195.description: Leo and Donnie disagree about their plan to stop the Kraang invasion. When Leo makes a critical mistake, he is separated from the team and Donnie must step up as a leader.

68196.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
68196.description: Po befriends a band of dancers, unaware they're actually a band of traveling thieves.

68197.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
68197.description: When the Furious 5 are all out of town and the Jade Palace is attacked, Po only has his dad and two old people to help him.

68198.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68198.description: When Kowalski's ray designed to freshen spoiled food accidentally hits Skipper before falling down a storm drain, the leader is turned into a baby penguin, albeit retaining much of Skipper's adult personality. // After learning of Savio's escape from Hoboken on a TV news report, the penguins organize an effort to protect the zoo from the vengeful boa.

68199.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68199.description: Kowalski’s obsession with Doris the dolphin drives him to invent a love ray, the Love-U-Laser. It works like a charm until Alice falls for a trashcan, Julien falls for Mort, and Skipper orders the ray to be put in reverse. Private gets hit by the reverse ray and instantly loathes Kowalski. Matters get much worse as the loathe ray explodes and everybody hates Kowalski! He’s only got one shot to stop being the most loathed penguin in the world. // Told as a courtroom flashback, Kowalski unwisely revives Jiggles in a small, whipped cream-eating version. The little green cubes multiply on impact, however, and are soon threatening to cover the surface of the earth. As the Jiggli multiply out of control, will the team be able to prevent the jiggli-fication of the world?

68200.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68200.description: When a gang of kids steals the Krusty Krab's grill, SpongeBob and Mr. Krabs go to extreme lengths to win it back. // SpongeBob helps out the Krusty Krab's night shift crew, but the customers crave something creepier than usual.

68201.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68201.description: SpongeBob visits his old pal Bubble Buddy's hometown... Bubbletown! // Sandy invites Karen and Mrs. Puff out for a night on the town, so the ladies decide to blow off some steam.

68202.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68202.description: SpongeBob and Patrick have their peaceful day of jelly fishing disturbed by Sandy's competitive nature. // SpongeBob pulls from Squidward's shirt a loose string that never seems to end.

68203.title: Nella The Princess Knight
68203.description: Nella and her friends discover a kingdom in the clouds. // When Trinket and Olivia are turned into icky lizards, Nella and the gang must find the antidote.

68204.title: Nella The Princess Knight
68204.description: Nella, Garrett and Blaine compete for an annual bravery award with chaotic consequences. // Badalf the Wicked Wizard steals a magical saber that can turn things into sand.

68205.title: Bubble Guppies
68205.description: Meet Monty - the loneliest (and only-est) rhinoceros in the zoo. He needs a friend, and Gil and the Bubble Guppies are determined to help while learning all about habitats at the zoo!

68206.title: Bubble Guppies
68206.description: Once upon a time, Molly and Gil went up a hill to fetch a pail of water. But when a mean Witch, played by Wanda Sykes, turns Bubble Puppy into a frog, Molly and Gil enlist the help of some famous fairytale friends to undo her mean green spell.

68207.title: Dora the Explorer
68207.description: Achoo, achoo! What's that sound? Benny the Bull has the sneezes. It's Doctor Dora to the rescue as she sets off to Benny's Barn for a house call.

68208.title: Dora the Explorer
68208.description: Yee haw! Cowgirl Dora and Cowboy Boots are riding through the Wild West on Pinto the Pony Express. They have to deliver a special package of cowboy cookies to Benny the Bull, but they'll have to be on the lookout for Swiper.

68209.title: Rusty Rivets
68209.description: When Mr. Higgins accidentally fills a GIANT beach ball with water instead of air, it's up to the gang to get it to the lake without popping so it doesn't flood the town. // Rusty and Ruby get stranded on an island when they compete to see who can pick up the most garbage at the lake.

68210.title: Rusty Rivets
68210.description: Liam wants to visit an amusement park, but obstacles in the way delay them from getting there in time, so Rusty makes a theme park just for him. // Rusty builds a big vacuum to clean up Liam's mess and find his screwdriver but the megavac starts to suck up too much!

68211.title: Blaze And The Monster Machines
68211.description: When Crusher tries to cheat at a carnival game, he accidentally strands himself and Pickle on a giant rocket! Now it’s up to Blaze and AJ to rescue the two trucks before their runaway rocket crashes into the garbage dump.

68212.title: Blaze And The Monster Machines
68212.description: Gabby, Blaze and AJ are out in the wilderness when they get a call, Blaze's friends have come down with a sickness called the Sneezles! Our heroes must race back to Axle City to bring the sick trucks the medicine oil they need.

68213.title: PAW Patrol
68213.description: It’s the annual Mayor’s Race, and Mayor Humdinger is planning his most devious cheating scheme yet. // When Ryder comes across a map for buried treasure, Mayor Humdinger snatches the map and runs off to find the loot for himself.

68214.title: PAW Patrol
68214.description: The PAW Patrol plan a special celebration for Wally the Walrus. When he doesn't show up, they find he has a special new friend named Walinda! // During Cap’n Turbot's archaeological dig, a rock slide unearths a big dinosaur bone!

68215.title: PAW Patrol
68215.description: Cap’n Turbot and his cousin Francois are whale watching when the Flounder hits a rock and starts to sink! This rescue needs all paws on deck. // Stowaway penguins have scattered around Adventure Bay! Time to call the PAW Patrol!

68216.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68216.description: SpongeBob and Patrick go to see the latest horror film, only to be seemingly stalked by the villain. // SpongeBob holds a séance at the Krusty Krab to learn the recipe for a long-lost sandwich.

68217.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68217.description: SpongeBob will do anything to get to meet his newest hero, Kenny The Cat. // Attempting to get more work out of Squidward, Mr. Krabs spins the story of the monstrous Yeti Crab, which eats lazy workers.

68218.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68218.description: In order to save money, Mr. Krabs fires SpongeBob. Unable to just “do nothing”, SpongeBob decides to go back to work doing anything, anywhere.

68219.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68219.description: Private's in heaven - icy, freezing heaven. The Lunacorns on Ice extravaganza is in town, and Skipper's determined to take him as a treat. Accompanied by unexpected fellow fanboys Bing and Roy, the gang heads to the arena. Things get a bit d-icey when the gorilla and rhino end up on the ice with the lunacorns. The enraged director is ready to shutter the whole thing unless they find some way to slip 'n slide out of it. Showdown on Fairway 18:A legendary putter is at the center of controversy when the Amarillo Kid returns to the zoo. The slippery armadillo needs Private's help to make good on an ill-advised bet with two gopher brothers. Who's the bad guy here though? The gophers show up at the zoo to actually warn the penguins about the kid! The story takes us on more twists and turns than a Pebble Beach golf hole!

68220.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68220.description: King Julien's archrival, Clemson, returns in another attempt to claim the lemur crown. This time the sneaky lemur has a document that "proves" King Julien is not the legitimate king because he wasn't born in Madagascar. A series of challenges to prove who's more kingly ensues, and the penguins try to stack the deck in Julien's favor by each switching brains with him. Simple, right? How could a plan like this possibly fail? Private and the Winky Factory: Private's favorite treat, the Peanut Butter Winky, is going the way of the dinosaur. Distraught that the snack cake is ceasing production, Private urges a raid on the Winky Factory where the last remaining Winkies are rolling off the production line. Impressed by Private's passion, Skipper gives him command of the mission! The young penguin learns there's a heck of a lot to digest when leading a team.

68221.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
68221.description: After Po gets trapped in a hole, Fung helps him out and is owed a favor. Will it be a costly one?

68222.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
68222.description: To impress his fan club, Po releases the Mongolian Fist Demon. Now he has to figure out how to defeat the Demon and save the village and his fans!

68223.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
68223.description: While the Mighty Mutanimals lay siege to TCRI, the Turtles must brave the bizarre world of Dimension X to save the enslaved people of New York.

68224.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
68224.description: Casey Jones thinks he can take on the criminal underworld on his own, but he soon finds himself in over his head.

68225.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68225.description: When SpongeBob suddenly becomes the richest citizen of Bikini Bottom, he finds himself surrounded by lots of new "friends" who are more than happy to help him spend his money. // It's the day of Squidward's big lead solo audition with the Bikini Bottom Men's Chorus, and Squidward is brimming with excitement. He's positive he's a shoo-in for the part.

68226.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68226.description: Mr. Krabs hatches up yet another get-rich-quick scheme: professional wrestling! But Mr. Krabs isn't the one who's going to wrestle. // The new Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy trading cards are on sale, and SpongeBob is determined to get the super special rare talking card, no matter how many packs of cards he needs to buy to find it.

68227.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68227.description: There's a new Viking-themed promotion at the Krusty Krab, so SpongeBob is determined to find out everything there is to know about Vikings. And what better way to find out about Vikings than to talk to them himself? // Mermaidman and Barnacleboy are having a book signing, but SpongeBob can't go because he has boating school. After some convincing, Patrick finally gets SpongeBob to take a bathroom break from class.

68228.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
68228.description: A rash of thefts in the Valley of Peace has the villagers in uproar and things only get worse when the culprit appears to be... Monkey?

68229.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
68229.description: Po's Kung Fu hero, Kwan the Unkillable, comes to the Valley of Peace and appears to be a feeble old man. Po agrees to stage a fight to help him get back on top. But Kwan may not be as weak as he looks.

68230.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68230.description: The Commissioner flips his lid, literally. His toupee blows off and sticks to Maurice, who also gets red cheeks and a skinned tail, all by accident. Julien and Mort chase him with sticks, intent on beating the “monster” stuck to Maurice’s head. The baboon ladies take Maurice in, protecting and pampering him because they mistakenly think he’s a male baboon. It’s up to the penguins to get the toupee back and restore it to its rightful scalp. // Shelly the ostrich gets stuck in drying cement and only Rico can save her. Shelly falls for him hard as a result, however, Rico’s heart forever belongs to his doll. Shelly swipes the doll and tries hard to win his heart, but Rico doesn’t budge and his doll is accidently hauled off in a recycle truck. The penguins give chase but are left hopelessly in the dust. Shelly, wanting to make amends, tosses them on her back and sprints after the truck – can she possibly catch it?

68231.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68231.description: The penguin’s worst nightmare has come true. After a sailing trip gone wrong they wind up in the Hoboken Zoo. Strangely, the animals are happy, the zoo is a paradise, and life couldn’t be better! Zookeeper Frances takes outstanding care of all of them – or does she? Something sinister bubbles under the surface – the happy animals are actually androids, and the real animals are held captive in a dungeon. They’re too messy and Zookeeper Frances can’t stand a mess! A rescue comes from a very unlikely source, and the final battle could go either way!

68232.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
68232.description: Leo and Donnie disagree about their plan to stop the Kraang invasion. When Leo makes a critical mistake, he is separated from the team and Donnie must step up as a leader.

68233.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
68233.description: The team comes to grips with the possibility that Leo won't get better, while things only get worse: a new mutant captures Raph!

68234.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68234.description: In order to save money, Mr. Krabs fires SpongeBob. Unable to just “do nothing”, SpongeBob decides to go back to work doing anything, anywhere.

68235.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68235.description: SpongeBob tries to take a shortcut to work, but becomes lost along the way. // After failing his driver’s test again, Mr. Krabs decides to teach SpongeBob how to drive himself.

68236.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68236.description: After receiving an invitation to a gallery opening, Squidward scrambles to find a friend to take with him. // While trying to order a special sandwich, Patrick gets swept up in the fast paced world of business.

68237.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
68237.description: Master Chao visits the valley to oversee a Tournament. Shifu is convinced that Po and Master Chao want to replace him. Shifu's old enemy, Pai Mei, arrives in the middle of the tournament and threatens to destroy Shifu.

68238.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
68238.description: Master Yao returns to the Jade Palace and announces that he's offering the Valley of Peace a one-day 'Wonder and Wisdom Exchange'. Anyone who brings him a new wonder will be allowed to ask him a single question.

68239.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68239.description: The notorious Vesuvius Twins have adopted Skipper and King Julien and brought the animal’s home to their luxury apartment. Not to spoil and pamper - but to fight each other over shiny baubles! The rest of the penguins and lemurs attempt a rescue but are captured themselves and made to perform in a painful “circus” the twins put together. The tables are going to need to be turned to get this circus out of town. // Kowalski has another breakthrough invention, tiny robots that group together and not only fix broken tools and appliances, but run them as well. The penguins can just sit back and let the “Nanites” take care of all their chores! The problem is, the Nanites are programmed to protect the penguins at all costs, and ultimately seal the birds inside their lair. The only way to escape is to do battle with a giant, nasty, Nanite robot.

68240.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68240.description: Private has an arch enemy in the form of Dale the snail. Why does this snail hate Private so much? It's because Private allegedly smashed the little guy, and keeps smashing him albeit accidentally. Even a public apology ends with Dale getting crushed. Sadly, Dale should never have been enemies with Private to begin with - it was a different penguin who did him wrong. // King Julien becomes enamored of a giant toilet the penguins have built. He wants to use it as his new throne, only the toilet is actually a stink bomb the penguins built to trap Dr. Blowhole. Julien accidently gets trapped, bound tightly to the bomb, so the penguins must try to stop it from detonating, all while going on a wild truck chase through New York. They end up in a New Jersey dump, and Skipper must show a sensitive side before all is lost.

68241.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
68241.description: While traveling towards the North Pole, the group almost gets captured by the Fire Nation. However, when a charismatic young man and his band of rebels attack the Fire Nation's camp and rescue them, the gang learns that the rebels are trying to resist the Fire Nation's motives to expand their territory. Katara and Aang really enjoy their time with the band of rebels, but Sokka soon discovers that they aren't as noble as meets the eye

68242.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
68242.description: When Aang and friends come to the rim of a giant canyon, they are asked to help guide two groups of refugees across. Aang quickly learns that this will be no easy task – the two tribes have been fighting for 100 years, not to mention the vicious wildlife living on the canyon floor.

68243.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68243.description: When stray snails start appearing around Bikini Bottom, SpongeBob decides to care for them himself. // To defend Bikini Bottom’s honor, Patrick enters a Krabby Patty eating competition.

68244.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68244.description: Patrick invents a new board game, and invites SpongeBob, Sandy and Squidward to play it with him. // After accidentally flushing Mr. Krabs’ safe, SpongeBob and Squidward must go into the sewers to find it.

68245.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68245.description: SpongeBob gets a pair of long pants, but they change his life in unexpected ways. // When Larry the Lobster opens a new gym in Bikini Bottom, SpongeBob becomes his best customer.

68246.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
68246.description: The Turtles discover Bigfoot in the woods, and Donnie befriends it, insisting they protect it from a hunter that is after it.

68247.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
68247.description: The team discovers a Kraang ship buried under April's house where they find... April's Mom! But as April reconnects with her lost mother, is she really all that she seems?

68248.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
68248.description: Po saves a girl from some bandits, only to learn that she's engaged to be married to the Dragon Warrior.

68249.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
68249.description: During a fight with Tong Fo, Po is struck by lightning, giving him the power to read minds.

68250.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68250.description: Marlene plans a game night to help the zoo animals bond but it takes a terrible turn when the snacks run out. While Kowalski, Maurice, and Mort go on a snack run the gaming animals begin to fight over the games - cheating, sore losing, unwilling participation… chaos! The snack runners get trapped by the law at the store, and the zoo animals have to reconcile quickly in order to pull off a risky rescue. This isn’t the kind of bonding Marlene had in mind! // Elmer the dog wants a friend, and thinks he found one in Mort. The penguins are compelled to rescue him, but Elmer doesn’t want to give the little lemur up! Max the cat is recruited to help, and Max uses his dog expertise to lead the boys to the giant dog. Mort is rescued, but at what cost? The penguins think Max has met his slobbery doom in the jaws of the giant mastiff.

68251.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68251.description: Kowalski's invention that stops time falls into the worst hands possible. King Julien's. The lemur promptly breaks it trapping the two of them in a world frozen in time. Instead of being a disaster, however, they realize they can do everything their hearts desire - invent like crazy, perform on Broadway, play tennis in the middle of the street. But even an infinite playland like this can't last forever! // Special Agent Buck Rockgut makes a "triumphant" return. While hunting the Red Squirrel across the globe, the crusty old bird contacts the penguins with a warning that the diabolical squirrel has a brainwashed sleeper agent among them. They battle each other to a standstill to uncover the agent - will it tear the unit apart? Can trust ever be restored? They have to take a trip to a faraway borough to uncover the truth.

68252.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
68252.description: Dr. Blowhole, uber nemesis of the Penguins, returns to New York with a plan so diabolical it plays like a symphony of evil.

68253.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
68253.description: Sandy tries to study SpongeBob and Patrick’s behavior, but her science experiment goes horribly awry. // Mr. Krabs takes Plankton’s advice, and finally marries the only thing he ever loved…money!

74583.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
74583.description: Pearl gets a job to be cool like her friends, but the only store that’s hiring is the lamest store at the mall! // SpongeBob loses the use of his thumbs, and must get them back in working order before his entire life falls apart.
